{"CHAT":[{"def":"To talk in a light and familiar manner; to converse without form or ceremony; to gossip.","pos":""}],"CHATEAU":[{"def":"A castle or a fortress in France.","pos":""},{"def":"A manor house or residence of the lord of the manor; a gentleman's country seat; also, particularly, a royal residence; as, the chateau of the Louvre; the chateau of the Luxembourg.","pos":""}],"CHATELAINE":[{"def":"An ornamental hook, or brooch worn by a lady at her waist, and having a short chain or chains attached for a watch, keys, trinkets, etc.","pos":""}],"CHATELET":[{"def":"A little castle.","pos":""}],"CHATELLANY":[{"def":"Same as Castellany.","pos":""}],"CHATI":[{"def":"A small South American species of tiger cat (Felis mitis).","pos":""}],"CHATOYANT":[{"def":"Having a changeable, varying luster, or color, like that of a changeable silk, or oa a cat's eye in the dark.","pos":""}],"CHATOYMENT":[{"def":"Changeableness of color, as in a mineral; play of colors.","pos":""}],"CHATTEL":[{"def":"Any item of movable or immovable property except the freehold, or the things which are parcel of it.","pos":""}],"CHATTELISM":[{"def":"The act or condition of holding chattels; the state of being a chattel.","pos":""}],"CHATTER":[{"def":"To utter sounds which somewhat resemble language, but are inarticulate and indistinct.","pos":""},{"def":"To talk idly, carelessly, or with undue rapidity; to jabber; to prate.","pos":""}],"CHATTERATION":[{"def":"The act or habit of chattering.","pos":""}],"CHATTERER":[{"def":"A bird of the family Ampelidæ -- so called from its monotonous note.","pos":""}],"CHATTERING":[{"def":"The act or habit of talking idly or rapidly, or of making inarticulate sounds; the sounds so made; noise made by the collision of the teeth; chatter.","pos":""}],"CHATTINESS":[{"def":"The quality of being chatty, or of talking easily and pleasantly.","pos":""}],"CHATTY":[{"def":"Given to light, familiar talk; talkative.","pos":""}],"CHATWOOD":[{"def":"Little sticks; twigs for burning; fuel.","pos":""}]}